    <section id="realistic-earnings">
      <h2>4. What You Can Realistically Earn</h2>
      <div class="table-scroll">
      <table>
        <tr><th>Method</th><th>Typical Monthly Range (10–15 hrs/week)</th><th>Pausable?</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Freelance writing</td><td>$200–$600</td><td>Fully</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Transcription</td><td>$150–$400</td><td>Fully</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Print-on-demand</td><td>$0–$300 (highly variable)</td><td>Batchable, not live</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Affiliate marketing</td><td>$0–$400 (builds over months)</td><td>Fully</td></tr>
      </table>
      </div>
      <p>Most parents in this situation earn $200–$800 a month working roughly 10–15 hours a week — a real, meaningful supplemental income, not a full-time replacement in the first few months.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="choosing-fit">
      <h2>5. Choosing the Right Fit for Your Household</h2>
      <p>Match the method to your actual interruption pattern, not the one you wish you had. A toddler who naps reliably for two predictable hours suits naptime-batchable work well. A toddler with no predictable nap suits fully pausable work (writing, transcription) better, since there's no reliable block to plan around.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="mistakes">
      <h2>6. Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="pc-card good">
          <h3>Do</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Choose one method that matches your actual interruption pattern</li>
            <li>Start with pausable work if your schedule is unpredictable</li>
            <li>Treat the first month as income validation, not a verdict</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="pc-card bad">
          <h3>Don't</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Commit to a live-shift job without reliable, consistent childcare</li>
            <li>Try to batch naptime work if naps are unpredictable</li>
            <li>Compare your first month to someone else's third year</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

